race.comment: PACIFIC GLAMOUR (10) resumed for her second career run with an impressive maiden win here over this route, scoring by 3.5 lengths as favourite. She maps for a beautiful run here tagging the speed and looks to have a fair bit more upside than her rivals. Takes plenty of beating again. MAJESTICITY (4) is going well, coming off her best run for the campaign last start when second at Ararat. She draws softly and can be in this a long way. NIGHT FLASH (7) resumes. His form tapered off at the end of last campaign but his best figures have him in the mix and he may have improved with a bit more maturity. NO SURRENDER (1) has a big weight off a very long spell so tread lightly but his best form last time in was in better races than this. FAITHINHER (6) resumes with minor claims.
